<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Prepare_private_subnets">Prepare private subnets</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=Operations_Bridge:2019.05/SubNOpsB&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=1" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" title="Edit section: Prepare private subnets">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=Operations_Bridge:2019.05/SubNOpsB&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1" title="Edit section: Prepare private subnets">edit source</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<p>A private subnet is a subnet associated with a route table that has a route to a NAT gateway. In a private subnet, the network traffic is isolated from internet and only local VPC network traffic is permitted. In every Availability Zone, a private subnet is required so as to launch EC2 instances as master/works nodes. You can use an existing subnet or create a new one.
</p>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Create_new_private_subnets">Create new private subnets</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=Operations_Bridge:2019.05/SubNOpsB&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=2" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" title="Edit section: Create new private subnets">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=Operations_Bridge:2019.05/SubNOpsB&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2" title="Edit section: Create new private subnets">edit source</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<p>In this example installation procedure, we are going to create 3 private subnets. To do this, follow these steps:
</p>
<ol><li>Open the Amazon VPC console at:&nbsp;<a target="1" rel="nofollow" class="external free" href="https://console.aws.amazon.com/vpc/home#subnets">https://console.aws.amazon.com/vpc/home#subnets</a>.<br></li>
<li>In the navigation pane, select&nbsp;<b>Subnets &gt; Create Subnet</b>.<br><a onclick="javascript:loadingImage(this);" class="image"><img alt="OpsBridge2019.02Subnet1.jpg" src="/mediawiki/images/a/a4/OpsBridge2019.02Subnet1.jpg" width="543" height="311" data-file-width="543" data-file-height="311"></a><br></li>
<li>Configure the subnet settings.<br><a onclick="javascript:loadingImage(this);" class="image"><img alt="OpsBridge2019.02Subnet2.jpg" src="/mediawiki/images/4/49/OpsBridge2019.02Subnet2.jpg" width="1172" height="503" data-file-width="1172" data-file-height="503"></a>
<ul><li>Set a good&nbsp;Name tag&nbsp;for easy identification in the future.</li>
<li>Select the VPC created in the previous step&nbsp;<a href="./itom/SMAX:2019.02/CreateVpcInstance" title="SMAX:2019.02/CreateVpcInstance">VPC preparation</a>.</li>
<li>Select an Availability Zone (make sure the 3 private subnets are distributed in different zones).</li>
<li>Select a good&nbsp;IPv4 CIDR block&nbsp;for each subnet.</li></ul></li>
<li>Repeat the steps above to create another 2 private subnets.<br></li></ol>
