<h4><span class="mw-headline" id="Associate_a_NAT_gateway_route_table_with_the_three_private_subnets">Associate a NAT gateway route table with the three private subnets</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=Operations_Bridge:2019.05/SubNOpsB&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=3" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" title="Edit section: Associate a NAT gateway route table with the three private subnets">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=Operations_Bridge:2019.05/SubNOpsB&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3" title="Edit section: Associate a NAT gateway route table with the three private subnets">edit source</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h4>
<p>Follow these steps:
</p>
<ol><li>Associate the route table with the three private subnets that you prepared.<a onclick="javascript:loadingImage(this);" class="image"><img alt="OpsBridge2019.02Subnet8.jpg" src="/mediawiki/images/1/1a/OpsBridge2019.02Subnet8.jpg" width="1283" height="556" data-file-width="1283" data-file-height="556"></a></li>
<li>In the navigation pane, select&nbsp;<b>Subnets</b>. Locate the three private subnets that you prepared.</li>
<li>Associate the private subnets with the NAT gateway route table.</li></ol>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Prepare_public_subnets">Prepare public subnets</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=Operations_Bridge:2019.05/SubNOpsB&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=4" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" title="Edit section: Prepare public subnets">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=Operations_Bridge:2019.05/SubNOpsB&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4" title="Edit section: Prepare public subnets">edit source</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<p>A public subnet is a subnet associated with a route table that has a route to an Internet gateway. In every Availability Zone, a public subnet is required so as to associate with the internet-facing application Load Balancer. You can use an existing subnet or create a new one.
</p>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Create_public_subnets">Create public subnets</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=Operations_Bridge:2019.05/SubNOpsB&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=5" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" title="Edit section: Create public subnets">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=Operations_Bridge:2019.05/SubNOpsB&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5" title="Edit section: Create public subnets">edit source</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<p>In this example installation procedure, we are going to prepare 3 public subnets. As we already created 1 public subnet when creating the VPC, now we only need to create another two public subnets. To do this, follow these steps:
</p>
<ol><li>Open the Amazon VPC console at:&nbsp;<a target="1" rel="nofollow" class="external free" href="https://console.aws.amazon.com/vpc/home#subnets">https://console.aws.amazon.com/vpc/home#subnets</a>.</li>
<li>In the navigation pane, select&nbsp;<b>Subnets &gt; Create Subnet</b>.<br><a onclick="javascript:loadingImage(this);" class="image"><img alt="OpsBridge2019.02Subnet3.jpg" src="/mediawiki/images/1/19/OpsBridge2019.02Subnet3.jpg" width="543" height="311" data-file-width="543" data-file-height="311"></a></li>
<li>Configure the subnet settings.</li>
<li>Repeat the steps above to create another public subnet.</li></ol>
